# Cursor Rules for Notes Project

## Code Style
- Use consistent indentation (2 spaces for JS/TS, 4 for Python)
- Prefer descriptive variable and function names
- Keep functions focused and single-purpose
- Use meaningful commit messages

## Documentation
- All markdown files should have proper frontmatter
- Use clear headings and structure
- Include examples where helpful
- Keep documentation concise but complete

## Project Structure
- Maintain the existing folder organization
- Add new content in appropriate sections
- Keep related files together
- Use consistent naming conventions

## Development Workflow
- Test changes locally before committing
- Use the Makefile for Docker operations
- Keep the website lean and fast
- Follow Docusaurus best practices

## Content Guidelines
- Write for clarity and understanding
- Use consistent formatting across similar content types
- Include context and explanations
- Keep notes organized and searchable

